The 59th Airport Council International (ACI) Africa Regional Conference and Exhibition kicked off in Lagos during the weekend. Hundreds of delegates and participants have arrived the country for the conference holding on the theme, ‘Business Transformation for Sustainable Development of African Airports.’ The week-long event kicked off on Saturday with the arrival of participants while the exhibition stand was opened yesterday at the Oriental Hotel venue of the conference. The event is expected to be declared open today by the Secretary to the Government of the Federation, Mr. Boss Mustapha while the Minister of State for Aviation, Sen. Hadi Sirika, President of Council, International Civil Aviation Organisation (ICAO), Dr. Bernard Aliu and Director-General, ACI World, Ms. Angela Gittens, would be in attendance. The President of ACI-Africa and Managing Director of the Federal Airports Authority of Nigeria (FAAN), the host of the conference, Engr. Saleh Dunoma said the country would leverage on the conference to secure significant buy-in into the several policies of President Muhammadu Buhari in growing the aviation sector. “Conference sessions will feature industry experts who will share their experience of technologies, innovations, strategies, mindset and models (e.g. public-private partnerships) to improve operations and boost revenue,” he said.